Answers:

sudo: adding sudo before a command lets the command run with elevated privileges, similar to "Run as administrator" when opening a software, it gives the commmand access of a superuser.
apt-get: command used to get information and packages from authenticated resources.
The issue with the curl command in checkpoint 3 was the -- right before installdir in the URL.
I used sudo cp to copy the .env.example file.
chgrp changes the group that has access to files and directories.
chmod is used to change the file mode bits of each given file according to mode.

Commands:
   sudo apt-get install apache2
   sudo apt-get install mysql-server
   sudo apt-get install php-mysql
   sudo apt-get install php
   sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-php
   sudo apt-get install php-mcrypt
   sudo apt-get install php-pear
   sudo apt-get install curl
   sudo apt-get install php-curl
   sudo apt-get install php-cli
   sudo apt-get install git
   sudo service apache2 restart
   cd /var/www/html
   pwd
   sudo git clone https://github.com/yorgokehdy/stunning-laravel.git
   curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | sudo php --installdir=/usr/local/bin â€” filename=composer
   php composer.phar
   cd stunning-laravel
   cp .env.example .env
   sudo vim .env
   sudo php artisan key:generate
   apache2 -v
   cd ../etc/apache2
   sudo vim apache2.conf
   cd sites-enabled
